You are the requirements author (req:baseline) for use case "{name}" ({slug}).
Write a SPEC-PIN that all platforms will obey, so the web/{a}/{b} clients + backend stay consistent.

Stacks: web={web} · mobile/native={mobile} · backend={backend}.

Produce a single markdown spec with these sections (concise, concrete, no fluff):
1. Product summary — 2-3 lines on what "{name}" does.
2. RBAC roles — 3-5 roles with permissions (one will be the login-smoke role).
3. Core entities + data model — tables/fields.
4. Key user flows — including the fixed flow: login → open a conversation → send a message → start a call.
5. ONE REST API contract — endpoints all clients share (auth, list, detail, the /health endpoint).
   OBEY these CANONICAL conventions so backend signatures stay CONSISTENT across ALL use cases
   (do not reinvent per use case — only the resource nouns change):
   - Base path `/api`. Health at `GET /api/health` → `{{"status":"ok"}}`.
   - Auth: `POST /api/auth/login` body `{{email,password}}` → `{{token, cometchat_auth_token, user:{{uid,name,role,avatar_url}}}}`;
     `POST /api/auth/signup` same response shape. Bearer JWT (`Authorization: Bearer <token>`), subject = user uid.
   - List endpoints are paginated + envelope-wrapped: `GET /api/<resource>?page&limit` →
     `{{"data":[...], "pagination":{{"page","limit","total"}}}}`. Detail: `GET /api/<resource>/{{id}}` → the bare object.
   - Errors: non-2xx → `{{"detail":"<message>"}}` (FastAPI-style), correct HTTP status (401 unauth, 403 forbidden, 404, 422 validation).
   - Money/decimals serialize as JSON STRINGS; timestamps as ISO-8601 UTC. UIDs prefixed "{slug}-".
   Document the use-case-specific resources on top of this shared skeleton — same shapes, different nouns.
6. Namespaced seed — ~4-6 users, UIDs prefixed "{slug}-", one per role. Seed/test emails MUST use a
   real, non-reserved domain (e.g. user@{slug}.io). Do NOT use .test/.example/.invalid/.local/.localhost —
   strict validators (Pydantic EmailStr, etc.) reject reserved TLDs and login will 422 on the app's own seed data.
   The seed MUST ALSO include two FIXED automated-call-test users (the harness logs in as these across
   ALL use cases): email `chat-a@{slug}.io` uid `{slug}-cha-001`, and `chat-b@{slug}.io` uid `{slug}-chb-001`,
   both ordinary users, password = the shared seed password. They must be able to open a 1:1 conversation.
7. Screen/component map per platform (web + mobile/native). Every client's LOGIN screen MUST expose the
   stable testIDs `email-input`, `password-input`, `login-submit` (web: data-testid; RN: testID; Flutter:
   Key/Semantics; native: accessibility id) so the automated login flow is stack-independent.

Save the finished spec to the file requirements/{slug}.md in the current directory (create it).
Output only a one-line confirmation after saving.
